# Lock all text files to LF in the repo + working tree on every platform.
# Without this, Windows checkouts (`core.autocrlf=true`) introduce CRLF and any
# tool that writes LF (biome, prettier, most editors) flags every line as
# "modified" on the next `git diff`, producing massive phantom diffs.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary declarations — git's content-sniffing usually catches these,
# but being explicit avoids accidental text-mode corruption on edge cases.
bun.lockb binary
*.lockb binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.db binary

# SVGs are text (XML) — keep default eol=lf.
*.svg text eol=lf
